</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF9368F2921FFBF20FFE4BE96BD9609" blockId="10.[136,1452,1674,1876]" pageId="10" pageNumber="255">
Recognised in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C464D0C2921FFBF21F3E4BE9694979A" authorityName="Forsskal" authorityYear="1775" box="[388,452,1674,1695]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Primulaceae" genus="Maesa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="10" pageNumber="255" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B932EA9D2921FFBF21F3E4BE9694979A" box="[388,452,1674,1695]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="255">Maesa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the combination of the following characters: obovate to oblanceolate leaves, entire leaf margins, pentamerous flowers, non-overlapping triangular calyx lobes, long hypanthium (more than 
<quantity id="4CBE9B6A2921FFBF2446E49A932B97C6" box="[1073,1147,1710,1732]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="255" unit="mm" value="0.6">0.6 mm</quantity>
long), simple racemes, solitary or fasciculate with more than 15 flowers per inflorescence, and the flowers with non-overlapping triangular calyx lobes and the hypanthium 0.7â€“1.00 mm long.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
