<paragraph id="8BF9368F2921FFBE20FFE5B6936C9325" blockId="10.[136,1452,1922,2093]" lastBlockId="11.[136,1452,158,941]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="256" pageId="10" pageNumber="255">
Small treelet. 
<emphasis id="B932EA9D2921FFBF215DE5B696E69699" box="[298,438,1922,1948]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="255">Indumentum</emphasis>
: all parts lacking hairs, scaly on lamina surfaces, buds, inflorescences and fruits; scales peltate, up to 
<quantity id="4CBE9B6A2921FFBF215FE592969D96C4" box="[296,461,1958,1985]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="255" unit="mm" value="0.07" valueMax="0.1" valueMin="0.04">0.04â€“0.10 mm</quantity>
in diameter, creamâ€“ginger, Â± sessile, circular with irregular margins. 
<emphasis id="B932EA9D2921FFBF2498E592920996C5" box="[1263,1369,1958,1984]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="255">Branches</emphasis>
drying grey-brown with scattered lenticels, glabrous, scaly to densely scaly on young parts. 
<emphasis id="B932EA9D2921FFBF242BE5FF93FA96E1" box="[1116,1194,1995,2020]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="255">Leaves</emphasis>
: lamina obovate, 4.9â€“ 7.0 cm long, 
<quantity id="4CBE9B6A2921FFBF2156E5DA96F0990C" box="[289,416,2030,2057]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.1" metricValueMin="2.9" pageId="10" pageNumber="255" unit="cm" value="3.5" valueMax="4.1" valueMin="2.9">2.9â€“4.1 cm</quantity>
wide, sub-coriaceous, drying dark olive green above, tawny-brown below, adaxial surface glabrous, scaly when young, abaxial surface glabrous; base cuneate; margins entire; apex obtuse or sometimes acute; midrib drying reddish brown, glabrous both adaxially and abaxially; secondary veins 6â€“8 pairs, semicraspedodromous, indumentum as lamina; petiole 
<quantity id="4CBE9B6A2920FFBE2187E2F6953F91D8" box="[496,623,194,221]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" metricValueMax="1.1" metricValueMin="0.9" pageId="11" pageNumber="256" unit="cm" value="1.0" valueMax="1.1" valueMin="0.9">0.9â€“1.1 cm</quantity>
long, glabrous. 
<emphasis id="B932EA9D2920FFBE235DE2F7939F91D9" box="[810,1231,194,221]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="256">Staminate inflorescences and flowers</emphasis>
not seen. 
<emphasis id="B932EA9D2920FFBE2531E2F696779005" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="256">Pistillate inflorescences</emphasis>
lateral (axillary), racemes, solitary or fasciculate with up to 3 inflorescences per axil, 
<quantity id="4CBE9B6A2920FFBE2577E2D292049004" box="[1280,1364,230,257]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="256" unit="cm" value="4.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.0">4â€“5 cm</quantity>
long at anthesis, c. 
<quantity id="4CBE9B6A2920FFBE217EE33E96039020" box="[265,339,266,293]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="11" pageNumber="256" unit="cm" value="5.5">5.5 cm</quantity>
long in fruit, axis sparsely scaly; pedicels 1.5â€“3.0 mm long, scaly distally; bracts ovate to triangular, 
<quantity id="4CBE9B6A2920FFBE20FFE31A965F904C" box="[136,271,302,329]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="256" unit="mm" value="0.6" valueMax="0.7" valueMin="0.5">0.5â€“0.7 mm</quantity>
long, scaly to densely scaly, margins entire, apex acute; bracteoles Â±opposite, inserted at the base of short elongated stalk of the hypanthium, shape as bracts, (0.45â€“) 0.6â€“0.7 (â€“0.9) mm long, 
<quantity id="4CBE9B6A2920FFBE241EE36693A49068" box="[1129,1268,338,365]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="256" unit="mm" value="0.4" valueMax="0.5" valueMin="0.3">0.3â€“0.5 mm</quantity>
wide. 
<emphasis id="B932EA9D2920FFBE2531E366978A9095" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="256">Pistillate flowers</emphasis>
pentamerous, drying whitish cream; calyx lobes triangular, 
<quantity id="4CBE9B6A2920FFBE23F4E34293779094" box="[899,1063,374,401]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" metricValueMax="5.6" metricValueMin="4.4" pageId="11" pageNumber="256" unit="mm" value="0.5" valueMax="0.56" valueMin="0.44">0.44â€“0.56 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity id="4CBE9B6A2920FFBE2418E34293A79094" box="[1135,1271,374,401]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="256" unit="mm" value="0.7" valueMax="0.9" valueMin="0.5">0.5â€“0.9 mm</quantity>
wide, glabrous, margins entire to ciliate, apex acute; corolla tube c. 
<quantity id="4CBE9B6A2920FFBE22B9E3AE947490B0" box="[718,804,410,437]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="256" unit="mm" value="0.6">0.6 mm</quantity>
long, corolla lobes 
