<subSubSection id="C35C65042920FFBE20CAE01E96E49389" pageId="11" pageNumber="256" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BF9368F2920FFBE20CAE01E96E49389" blockId="11.[136,1452,158,941]" pageId="11" pageNumber="256">
<emphasis id="B932EA9D2920FFBE20CAE01E95569341" bold="true" box="[189,518,554,580]" pageId="11" pageNumber="256">Distribution and ecology:â€”</emphasis>
This species is currently known only from the 
<typeStatus id="54FD882D2920FFBE2471E01F93669340" box="[1030,1078,555,581]" pageId="11" pageNumber="256">type</typeStatus>
specimen collected from 
<collectingRegion id="4982F86D2920FFBE2524E01E97BE936D" country="Papua New Guinea" name="Morobe" pageId="11" pageNumber="256">Morobe Province</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F351761F2920FFBE208FE07B9682936D" box="[248,466,590,617]" name="Papua New Guinea" pageId="11" pageNumber="256">Papua New Guinea</collectingCountry>
. The plant was found as a small treelet in burn-maintained rangeland with 
<taxonomicName id="4C464D0C2920FFBE2575E07B92F4936D" authority=", Maotia" authorityName="Maotia" box="[1282,1444,591,617]" class="Cycadopsida" family="Cycadaceae" genus="Cycas" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cycadales" pageId="11" pageNumber="256" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B932EA9D2920FFBE2575E07B92F4936D" box="[1282,1444,591,617]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="256">Cycas, Maotia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C464D0C2920FFBE20C0E04696679389" box="[183,311,626,652]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Mussaenda" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="11" pageNumber="256" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B932EA9D2920FFBE20C0E04696679389" box="[183,311,626,652]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="256">Mussaenda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shrubbery.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C35C65042920FFBE20CAE0A293E992A8" pageId="11" pageNumber="256" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BF9368F2920FFBE20CAE0A2954F93FD" blockId="11.[136,1452,158,941]" pageId="11" pageNumber="256">
<emphasis id="B932EA9D2920FFBE20CAE0A2963493B5" bold="true" box="[189,356,662,688]" pageId="11" pageNumber="256">Etymology:â€”</emphasis>
The epithet is derived from the Latin word â€˜pusilliâ€™ and the word â€˜floraâ€™ to refer to its tiny flowers; to be precise, whilst all species of the genus have small flowers, the corolla of this species is obviously smaller comparative to the hypanthium size.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF9368F2920FFBE20CAE13693E992A8" blockId="11.[136,1452,158,941]" pageId="11" pageNumber="256">
<emphasis id="B932EA9D2920FFBE20CAE13696769219" bold="true" box="[189,294,770,796]" pageId="11" pageNumber="256">Notes:â€”</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C464D0C2920FFBE2151E13796A39219" authorityName="Sumanon &amp; Utteridge. A" authorityYear="2021" box="[294,499,770,796]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Primulaceae" genus="Maesa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="11" pageNumber="256" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pusilliflora">
<emphasis id="B932EA9D2920FFBE2151E13796A39219" box="[294,499,770,796]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="256">Maesa pusilliflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be distinguished by the combination of characters outlined in the diagnosis. It is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C464D0C2920FFBE2082E11396D19245" authorityName="Utteridge" authorityYear="2000" box="[245,385,806,832]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Primulaceae" genus="Maesa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="11" pageNumber="256" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="beamanii">
<emphasis id="B932EA9D2920FFBE2082E11396D19245" box="[245,385,806,832]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="256">M. beamanii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but it may be distinguished by floral merosity (pentamerous) and inflorescence structure (simple racemose with more than 15 flowers). This species is also similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C464D0C2920FFBE23E3E17F932A9261" authorityName="Sumanon &amp; Utteridge. A" authorityYear="2021" box="[916,1146,842,868]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Primulaceae" genus="Maesa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="11" pageNumber="256" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oblanceolatifolia">
<emphasis id="B932EA9D2920FFBE23E3E17F932A9261" box="[916,1146,842,868]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="256">M. oblanceolatifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, another new species from 
<collectingRegion id="4982F86D2920FFBE20FFE15A963A928D" box="[136,362,878,905]" country="Papua New Guinea" name="Milne Bay" pageId="11" pageNumber="256">Milne Bay Province</collectingRegion>
described in this paper; however, 
<taxonomicName id="4C464D0C2920FFBE229DE15B94DC928D" authorityName="Sumanon &amp; Utteridge. A" authorityYear="2021" box="[746,908,878,904]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Primulaceae" genus="Maesa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="11" pageNumber="256" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pusilliflora">
<emphasis id="B932EA9D2920FFBE229DE15B94DC928D" box="[746,908,878,904]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="256">M. pusilliflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C464D0C2920FFBE24B0E15B92FB928D" authorityName="Sumanon &amp; Utteridge. A" authorityYear="2021" box="[1223,1451,878,904]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Primulaceae" genus="Maesa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="11" pageNumber="256" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oblanceolatifolia">
<emphasis id="B932EA9D2920FFBE24B0E15B92FB928D" box="[1223,1451,878,904]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="256">M. oblanceolatifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the non-overlapping triangular calyx lobes and longer hypanthium (more than 
<quantity id="4CBE9B6A2920FFBE246DE1A6932092A8" box="[1050,1136,914,941]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="256" unit="mm" value="0.6">0.6 mm</quantity>
long).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
